# Plan — AI Chatbot for Customer Support
slug: ai-chatbot-for-customer-support | richness: 10/10 | build: FULL

---

## Demo concept

**"SupportAI" — In-browser AI chatbot embedded on a mock e-commerce support page.**

A production-quality support widget running a real LLM (Llama-3.2-1B via WebLLM/WebGPU) entirely in the browser — zero backend, zero token cost. Demonstrates all 5 client capabilities in a single live URL. Two entry points: the customer-facing chat widget (index.html) and the admin panel (admin.html).

Prototype vs full decision: **FULL.** All features are achievable client-side with WebLLM + Transformers.js. No prototype trigger fires.

---

## Architecture

```
Browser
├── model-loader.js  ← WebLLM (Llama-3.2-1B, WebGPU) → Transformers.js WASM → template-RAG fallback
├── rag.js           ← FAQ JSON corpus + cosine similarity retrieval (embeddings precomputed or runtime)
├── chat.js          ← orchestrates: retrieve context → LLM prompt → stream response → cite sources
├── order-api.js     ← mock orders.json lookup by order# or email
├── escalation.js    ← ET hours check (Date in America/New_York) + handoff form + simulated ticket#
└── admin.js         ← KB editor, deflection analytics, session log viewer
```

LLM chain (in order of availability):
1. **WebLLM** — `https://esm.run/@mlc-ai/web-llm` (v0.2.84), model `Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC` (WebGPU required, ~879 MB download, cached in IndexedDB)
2. **Transformers.js WASM** — `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@huggingface/transformers@4.2.0/+esm` (**NOT `@xenova/transformers`** — renamed in v3, frozen/EOL), instruction model `onnx-community/Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct` (`dtype:"q4", device:"wasm"`), embedding model `Xenova/all-MiniLM-L6-v2` (`dtype:"fp32", device:"wasm"`)
3. **Template fallback** — deterministic RAG-only: top-1 retrieved FAQ displayed verbatim + escalate if no match

**Critical deploy-test note:** Playwright headless Chromium has NO WebGPU — WASM path is what CI exercises. WASM must produce real coherent answers, not a skeleton. WebGPU is progressive enhancement only.

---

## Hero feature

**In-browser streaming chatbot with RAG + order lookup**

- Chat widget opens as floating bubble on any page (iFrame-embeddable via `<iframe src="...">`)
- Model load flow: progress bar, "AI loading... (running locally on your device, no data sent)", % done
- User types query → RAG retrieves top-3 FAQ chunks (cosine sim) → injected into LLM system prompt → streamed response
- Each response includes cited FAQ sources ("Based on our returns policy...")
- Order lookup: user says "where is my order 12345" → bot calls `lookupOrder('12345')` → injects status into prompt
- Graceful: if confidence low → escalation suggestion appears inline

## Supporting feature 1: Escalation + ET hours routing

- "Talk to a human" button always visible
- ET hours check on click: `Intl.DateTimeFormat` in `America/New_York`
  - Within 9am-6pm ET Mon-Fri: "Our team is available now — we'll respond within a few minutes." → handoff form
  - Outside hours: "Our team is offline until [next open time]." → leave-a-message form
- Form submits → animated "Ticket #[random 5-digit] created — you'll hear back at [email]" confirmation
- Simulated Zendesk: UI shows the ticket card in Zendesk-esque styling with tag `source: chatbot`

## Supporting feature 2: Admin panel (admin.html)

- **KB editor:** table of FAQ entries (question + answer + category); add/edit/delete; saved to localStorage
- **Analytics dashboard:** deflection rate (% conversations resolved without escalation), top 5 queries by frequency, handoff count, avg messages per session — all computed from sessionStorage log
- **Session viewer:** scrollable list of past chat sessions with transcript

